01:01:31.560 --> 01:01:35.880
If you start flailing around because of the unexpectedness, you're easily uprooted.

01:01:37.560 --> 01:01:43.400
If you just sort of lock in, your ability to sense what's going on and respond is lost.

01:01:43.400 --> 01:01:49.640
You want to find this optimal relationship between sensitivity and stability.

01:01:51.240 --> 01:01:54.360
Now you may be saying, well, I'm not going to get into any fights.

01:01:55.000 --> 01:01:58.680
I hope that's right, by the way, because when if you're fighting, even if you win,

01:01:58.680 --> 01:02:05.640
you lose. You lose a little piece of your soul. So what's the point of, well, the point is transfer.

01:02:06.440 --> 01:02:12.200
Think about entering into a situation in which you want to enter into a deep dialogue

01:02:13.480 --> 01:02:18.760
with another human being the way Socrates does. And Socrates is all just sort of scattered.

01:02:19.720 --> 01:02:29.320
Then his capacity for entering into the deep conversation is lost.

01:02:30.920 --> 01:02:36.680
But if he's just rigid and closed in upon himself and holding on to his position no matter what,

01:02:36.680 --> 01:02:42.600
you can't move me, I am so stable. It's true, I can't. But then what's the point of the conversation?

01:02:43.960 --> 01:02:47.320
How will the dialogue take? How will it lead both people?

01:02:49.000 --> 01:03:00.600
So you want to be sensitive yet stable, stable yet sensitive, so that you can optimally flow

01:03:01.240 --> 01:03:10.040
within any situation, especially situations of dialogical encounter. Being able to root,

01:03:10.360 --> 01:03:21.800
really important. So often when I'm doing these discussions that I have with people and engaging

01:03:21.800 --> 01:03:29.800
in these Socratic practices in a way that they might not know, I'm doing Tai Chi Chuan. They

01:03:29.800 --> 01:03:35.080
don't know it. Sometimes they do. I've had people look at one of my videos, especially when the

01:03:35.160 --> 01:03:40.680
other person was sort of very interruptive or hyperactive, and they'll say, you were like doing

01:03:40.680 --> 01:03:48.920
really good Tai Chi there. Yes, exactly. I take that as a very encouraging compliment for which

01:03:48.920 --> 01:03:56.200
I'm grateful because I aspire to that. I aspire to be able to have that rootedness so that I'm not

01:03:56.200 --> 01:04:03.320
easily overwhelmed, but I can also flow into the situation. I'm aware of what's going on.

01:04:03.560 --> 01:04:11.560
In the meditative tradition, this is called sitting as still as a mountain, but as alert as a warrior.

01:04:12.600 --> 01:04:16.840
This is a phrase used, by the way, within Buddhist traditions that are often committed to non-violence.

01:04:20.280 --> 01:04:28.200
So how do we do it? How do we do it? How do we get that? And how do we learn it in a way that can

01:04:28.280 --> 01:04:33.320
transfer to most of our life? Well, if you think about Taoism, you can think about

01:04:34.040 --> 01:04:41.560
that the very famous Yang Yin symbol with the black and the white and the black dot and the

01:04:41.560 --> 01:04:48.120
white dot and the white dot in the black area, showing that they're flowing. They have this

01:04:48.120 --> 01:04:50.600
flowing balance and they interpenetrate each other.

01:04:50.600 --> 01:05:01.480
We're trying to get a mind that is open, yet centered and stabilized.

01:05:03.080 --> 01:05:09.880
It can flow out into Yang, but it can also return to Yin,

01:05:11.320 --> 01:05:14.360
and it has these so that they interpenetrate each other.

01:05:14.520 --> 01:05:19.960
Now, how would you do this practice? Well, first of all,

01:05:22.120 --> 01:05:26.440
you go through your centering practice. You do all three centers. I won't repeat that now,

01:05:26.440 --> 01:05:33.960
but you make sure you center mind and body. You center your attention. You center your attitude.

01:05:33.960 --> 01:05:40.760
Get centered. Now, I'm going to describe the practice to you and what it looks like,

01:05:41.320 --> 01:05:45.240
what it feels like. Let's say you're centered. Your eyes are closed.

01:05:47.240 --> 01:05:49.640
I want you to imagine a space just slightly above your head,

01:05:51.080 --> 01:05:56.200
and then as you inhale, you're expanding in all directions, almost like you were inflating a balloon,

01:05:56.920 --> 01:06:02.680
a perfectly spherical balloon in all directions. You inhale. This is you opening up. This is you

01:06:02.680 --> 01:06:09.640
expanding your awareness, expanding your connection to the world. Right? As you inhale,

01:06:09.640 --> 01:06:13.400
don't hyperventilate, but you inhale and you expand.

