01:06:20.840 --> 01:06:29.800
This is the end. You come in. You come in. So inhale, exhale, and then you find that spot.

01:06:31.640 --> 01:06:35.480
Oh, right there. That's about right. Where it is for you is where it is for you.

01:06:36.440 --> 01:06:41.720
Don't imitate what I'm doing. Imitate the way I'm doing something.

01:06:44.760 --> 01:06:50.760
Inhale, exhale. And the last little bit of the exhale and that little space in between the breaths,

01:06:51.320 --> 01:06:57.240
it's like I'm opening and melting and draining, and I'm coming to what's called the third eye

01:06:57.320 --> 01:07:06.760
traditionally. And from there, but even from the center of my head on that axis, I inhale out,

01:07:09.080 --> 01:07:21.640
I exhale in, opening, melting, draining to the throat. Inhale, remember all directions, 360.

01:07:22.280 --> 01:07:27.160
Inhale, opening, exhale, gathering,

01:07:29.960 --> 01:07:32.200
opening, melting, draining to the heart.

01:07:35.880 --> 01:07:40.520
Inhale, opening, exhale, gathering,

01:07:42.920 --> 01:07:46.120
opening and melting and draining to the solar plexus.

01:07:46.120 --> 01:07:55.320
Inhale, opening, exhale, gathering and falling back towards the center.

01:07:55.320 --> 01:08:03.000
Yang into Yin, Yin into Yang. Do you see? Opening, melting, draining to this area called the Dantian.

01:08:03.880 --> 01:08:07.400
This is eventually where you want your breathing to be when you're meditating.

01:08:07.400 --> 01:08:13.720
Don't force it there. Let it naturally fall there over time. But here you center around there.

01:08:14.440 --> 01:08:18.280
The tradition says one finger below your navel, three fingers in.

01:08:21.720 --> 01:08:27.960
I don't know if that's precise, but something like that. Inhale, exhale.

01:08:29.480 --> 01:08:36.040
And then opening and melting, draining to where that center axis is touching what you're sitting on.

01:08:36.920 --> 01:08:42.040
Feel that point. Everything is drained there like a pool of liquid.

01:08:44.200 --> 01:08:51.080
And now you let it sink into the earth. Imagination for the sake of enhancing perception.

01:08:51.800 --> 01:08:57.800
You let it sink like the root of a tree, rooting. It's sinking into the earth, connecting you,

01:08:57.800 --> 01:09:05.000
stabilizing you downward, but also nourishing you, energizing you, sensitizing you upward

01:09:06.680 --> 01:09:11.640
so that you're then sitting as still as a mountain.

01:09:14.680 --> 01:09:20.760
But as alert, as a warrior. So you center, find your three centers.

01:09:22.280 --> 01:09:25.880
Go through that rooting practice. You may want to replay that sequence.

01:09:28.280 --> 01:09:30.360
So I can talk you through it while you're doing it.

01:09:32.280 --> 01:09:39.080
Once you feel that sweet spot, that optimal grip between Yin and Yang,

01:09:40.040 --> 01:09:47.000
you feel rooted into the earth, then begin your meditation, following your breath,

01:09:47.720 --> 01:09:54.280
labeling your distractions, befriending yourself. That is the rooting practice.

01:09:58.440 --> 01:10:02.760
The other practice is specifically oriented towards

01:10:03.640 --> 01:10:08.360
the learned ignorance that we've been talking about in this episode.

01:10:10.360 --> 01:10:17.720
This is a practice that I call the humble wonder practice. Humility and wonder were both

01:10:17.720 --> 01:10:28.280
central and integral to the Socratic practices, especially the practice of learned ignorance.

01:10:29.240 --> 01:10:39.160
How does this practice work? I recommend first centering and rooting and doing two or three

01:10:39.160 --> 01:10:48.200
minutes of basic meditation. Then bring your awareness to your heart area. You can put your

01:10:48.200 --> 01:10:51.960
hands on your heart. I won't put them right there because I don't want to screw up my mic.

01:10:52.280 --> 01:11:00.600
Then I say as mindfully, and you've been cultivating mindfulness now, I say as mindfully as I can.

01:11:04.360 --> 01:11:08.440
There is so much I do not know about myself because of all of the facts.

01:11:10.600 --> 01:11:14.680
There is so much you do not know about your mind, your psyche, your body,

01:11:15.320 --> 01:11:18.920
the amount of information available to you is combinatorial explosive.

01:11:19.480 --> 01:11:26.920
But instead of keeping it as a safe, propositional thing you store over here, you're realizing it.

01:11:29.720 --> 01:11:34.680
There is so much I do not know about myself because of all of the facts.

01:11:36.680 --> 01:11:41.720
If you want to add all the facts about myself, feel fine. Feel free to do so.

01:11:42.680 --> 01:11:49.640
Next, there is so much I shall never know about myself because of all of the

01:11:49.640 --> 01:11:55.320
faith. Faith, what do you mean by faith, John? I don't mean your cosmic destiny or something

01:11:55.320 --> 01:12:02.280
written down. I mean faith in the sense that it's in the word fatal. You're born at a particular

01:12:02.280 --> 01:12:07.960
time in a particular place. You're exposed to particular people, to particular events,

01:12:07.960 --> 01:12:14.440
none of which you have control over, and they deeply shape you. If you do not acknowledge

01:12:14.440 --> 01:12:21.080
your faith in that sense, your inherent finitude, then your capacity for really

01:12:21.720 --> 01:12:25.480
realizing your self-knowledge is truncated in hamstrung.

01:12:29.080 --> 01:12:34.840
There is so much I shall never know about myself because of all of the faith.

01:12:38.920 --> 01:12:41.480
Next, and they're all Fs to help you remember.

01:12:43.800 --> 01:12:49.720
There is so much I refuse to see about myself because of all of my foolishness.

01:12:53.720 --> 01:13:00.040
All the processes that make us adaptively intelligent make us perennially and sometimes

01:13:00.120 --> 01:13:12.760
pervasively beset by self-deception. How often? Be honest. Really honest, please. How often do

01:13:12.760 --> 01:13:20.280
you really, not in thought or in belief, but actually in perspective and in how you participate

01:13:20.280 --> 01:13:25.720
in your identity, how often do you actually challenge your egocentrism and the way it might be

01:13:25.720 --> 01:13:34.440
bias in you? Igor Grossman found, he asked people to describe a really hard problem they're

01:13:35.400 --> 01:13:39.880
involved in. They inevitably describe it from the first person perspective without thinking,

01:13:39.880 --> 01:13:45.800
automatic framing. And then if you say to them, and think about Socrates here, questioning people,

01:13:45.800 --> 01:13:51.800
if you say to them, well, can you re-describe that problem from a third person perspective,

01:13:51.800 --> 01:13:58.200
how your friend might see it and describe it? And will people do this? They inevitably have

01:13:58.200 --> 01:14:04.920
an insight. They realize, oh, I didn't see this. I didn't realize that. You know that what I'm saying

01:14:04.920 --> 01:14:13.080
is true. Think about how wise you are about other people's problems. Don't you realize it, Jim?

01:14:13.080 --> 01:14:18.920
You're doing that same self-destructive pattern in your romantic life. I can see it so clearly,

01:14:18.920 --> 01:14:25.800
and Jim is like, I don't really see it. And you think, ha, ha, ha, but then the roles are reversed

01:14:25.800 --> 01:14:31.720
and Jim is saying to you, hey, you're doing that thing you do with relationship to your career.

01:14:31.720 --> 01:14:35.880
You're doing it again. Don't you see? And you go, I don't really see it. You know that.

01:14:38.360 --> 01:14:44.520
Part of what we're going to learn in these Socratic practices is how to be Socrates

01:14:44.600 --> 01:14:49.400
for yourself. And that's inexorably bound up with how can we be Socrates to each other?

01:14:50.760 --> 01:14:59.080
Okay, so back first. Let's repeat. Let's review. There's so much I do not know about myself because

01:14:59.080 --> 01:15:08.520
of all of the facts. Realize it. Don't just state it. Live it. There's so much I shall never know

01:15:09.400 --> 01:15:15.160
about myself because of all of the fate. Realize it. Become into deep awareness. Make it real.

01:15:17.720 --> 01:15:21.720
There's so much I refuse to see because of all of my foolishness.

01:15:24.120 --> 01:15:36.360
Realize it. And then there is so much I'm unable to see about myself because of all of my faults.

01:15:39.480 --> 01:15:44.360
And you're probably saying, oh, this is a real downer. Stick with it. Stay with me.

01:15:45.960 --> 01:15:47.080
It doesn't end that way.

01:15:50.600 --> 01:15:52.280
Then you can turn your hands outward like this.

01:15:54.920 --> 01:16:03.000
We go through the same procedure. There is so much I don't know about the world because of all of the facts.

01:16:03.640 --> 01:16:10.920
There is so much I shall never know about the world because of all of the fate.

01:16:14.120 --> 01:16:18.440
There is so much I refuse to see about the world because of all of my foolishness.

01:16:23.000 --> 01:16:27.720
There is so much I am unable to see about the world because of all of my faults.

01:16:28.280 --> 01:16:36.840
Then relax your hands back down to your meditation. And here's now where it flips.

01:16:38.520 --> 01:16:43.960
You did the humility. And if it was just humility, it could be humiliating,

01:16:44.840 --> 01:16:53.320
but it's not just the humility. Now as I inhale, both inwardly and outwardly,

01:16:53.400 --> 01:16:59.720
I experience wonder, not curiosity, where I'm trying to find missing information.

01:16:59.720 --> 01:17:05.400
And we'll talk more about this, but wonder, where I'm able to call the world and myself

01:17:05.400 --> 01:17:13.960
into question, but in a way that is positive, that is enriching, that is growing me.

01:17:13.960 --> 01:17:22.280
As I inhale, I wonder into the center of my mind outward to the circumference of the world,

01:17:22.360 --> 01:17:32.200
inhaling, wondering, and then exhaling, receiving, receiving, being open to receiving from the world

01:17:32.200 --> 01:17:36.360
and receiving from the depths of my psyche, the depths of the world and the depths of the psyche,

01:17:36.360 --> 01:17:44.200
receiving, inhaling, wonder, wondering inward, wondering outward.

01:17:44.600 --> 01:17:54.440
Exhale, receiving, receiving from the depths of the psyche, receiving from the depths of the world.

01:18:00.440 --> 01:18:10.120
Do that practice with the breath at least four times. You may want to do it longer

01:18:10.120 --> 01:18:17.320
and get the sense of the wonder and the receptivity actually interpenetrating,

01:18:19.240 --> 01:18:25.880
mutually affording and enriching each other, so that you have wonder filled receptivity,

01:18:25.880 --> 01:18:32.520
wonderful, wonderful receptivity. You have a profound humility,

01:18:33.400 --> 01:18:43.000
but a transcendent wonder. That is the humble wonder of practice.

01:18:45.160 --> 01:18:52.200
I recommend still doing your basic meditation practice, centering and rooting,

01:18:54.040 --> 01:19:01.640
and then do this practice, both sides of it. The humility practice and the wonder side

01:19:03.000 --> 01:19:07.320
and that usually only takes about five to ten minutes. You can shave a little bit off

01:19:07.320 --> 01:19:12.440
the meditation if you really want to limit yourself to staying under 25 minutes in total,

